Grizzly Class of 2020,

Friday, May 1, 2020 from 6:00 to 8:00 pm will be the time for you to come and pick up your Senior Signs. Faculty has been invited as well to give you a Senior send off. The signs will be located on the front lawn of the main building on campus. Please come and collect your sign at this time. If you are unable to attend at this time arrangements will be made to get your sign to you. Remember social distancing and guidelines are still in effect, loitering will not be allowed. post_text:
Tonight, April 10, 2020 at 8:20 pm come join Labette County High School and other school districts across our State and Nation for the Be The Light campaign. This is to celebrate the Senior class of 2020 and spring sports, coaches, and families.

The lights at Lucas Stadium, Vic George Field, and the Denzil Davidson sports complex will go on at 8:20 pm for 20 minutes as a symbol that we are thinking of them and we will eventually return to school and competition.

Persons hoping to witness this event are encouraged to drive by the venues and provide support by honking your car horn a time or two. Participants are to remain in their vehicles in order to adhere to the social distancing guidelines. #beAGrizzly #weRLabette #SR2020 #beTHElight

USD 506 is Now Hiring!

USD 506 Labette is now accepting applications for a Facility & Maintenance Worker. Duties associated with this position include maintenance, repair, & installation of HVAC systems, plumbing, boilers, electrical, carpentry, exterior & interior of buildings and school grounds, and other duties as assigned. Requires physical exertion and applicants must be able to work indoors & outdoors year-round. This assignment is a year-round position. Applicants will have at least 2 years of HVAC experience (Preferred), & be able to diagnose & trouble shoot electrical components. A complete job description is available on the district website. Applications may be submitted on line at www.usd506.org or picked up at the District Office located at 401 S. High School Street, Altamont, KS 67330.

post_text:
Mound Valley 8th Grade Students Learning CPR!!!

Did You Know? Every 8th Grader enrolled in USD 506 learns CPR and First Aid! There is value to learning CPR--At Any AGE!

Having someone in your family who knows CPR just may save a life someday. Including your own.

According to the American Heart Association, approximately 350,000 people experience cardiac arrest every year in the United States. Most of those occur outside of a hospital. Of those, 90% do not survive. This is mainly because they do not get help quick enough.

2019-2020 Labette County High School Kansas Honors Scholars were honored last night in a ceremony at Pittsburg High School.

To be nominated, students must be graduating seniors who rank in the top 10 percent of their class, based on academic records through the previous semester.

They receive a Kansas Honor Scholars Program certificate and a distinctive medallion for students to wear at their local graduation. This program is funded by the Alumni Association at the University of Kansas.

Pictured are (from left to right) Clara Rucker, Cloey Jones, Mattaya Gibbs, Jack Leake, Danielle Kelley, Isabelle Redford, and Hannah Shire.

Unable to attend and Not Pictured: Amelia Archer, Kaitlin Cartwright, Keeley Daniels, and David Rohling.

post_text:
SCHOOL BUS SAFETY WEEK

National School Bus Safety Week is October 21-15. Be sure to tell your favorite driver thanks for helping to make school happen each day! Here are some interesting and fun facts regarding school transportation at USD 506:

1. Our district covers over 500 square miles.
2. Nine Hundred (900) students are transported each day.
3. Our district has 25 bus routes.
4. Our district has 10 special education routes.
5. Total miles driven each day: 3,500.
6. Our vehicles consume 900 gallons of diesel each
month.
7. Our vehicles consume 4,500 gallons of unleaded fuel
each month.
8. Our bus drivers are exceptional!
